---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy | harder.dev" description="Privacy Policy for harder.dev and Harder Labs LLC.">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="muted">/privacy</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">
        This Privacy Policy explains how Harder Labs LLC (dba Harder Labs) collects and uses information on harder.dev.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose-block">
      <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> March 1, 2026</p>

      <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        harder.dev is operated by Harder Labs LLC, a Texas limited liability company. Contact: <a class="inline-link" href="mailto:kevin@harder.dev">kevin@harder.dev</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Information we collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Basic usage data:</strong> IP address, browser/device metadata, referrer, and page activity via standard web hosting and analytics logs.</li>
        <li><strong>Contact data:</strong> Information you provide when contacting us (such as name, email, and message content).</li>
        <li><strong>Transactional data:</strong> If a project under Harder Labs processes a purchase, payment details are handled by payment processors and not stored in full on this site.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. How we use information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Operate, secure, and improve our websites and services.</li>
        <li>Respond to inquiries and customer service requests.</li>
        <li>Support accounting, fraud prevention, compliance, and legal obligations.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Cookies and analytics</h2>
      <p>
        This site may use cookies or similar technologies for analytics and performance measurement. You can control cookies via your browser settings.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Sharing information</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell personal information. We may share information with service providers (hosting, analytics, email, payment, bookkeeping, legal/tax tools) when necessary to operate the business and fulfill obligations.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Data retention</h2>
      <p>
        We retain information only as long as needed for business operations, legal requirements, dispute resolution, and enforcement of agreements.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, or restrict certain processing of your personal information. To make a request, email us at
        <a class="inline-link" href="mailto:kevin@harder.dev">kevin@harder.dev</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Third-party links and project-specific policies</h2>
      <p>
        harder.dev may link to external sites and individual ventures under Harder Labs LLC. Those sites may maintain separate privacy policies and terms.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The "Last updated" date reflects the latest revision.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose-block {
    max-width: 72ch;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.7rem;
  }

  .prose-block h2 {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
  }

  .prose-block ul {
    margin-left: 1.2rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.35rem;
  }
</style>
